Back pain after an epidural is very common and can persist for weeks or even months after delivery. Thankfully, chiropractic care can help many women find safe and natural pain relief from epidural side effects.

There are many movements which can contribute to back pain after childbirth, including:
Having An Epidural
Pushing During Delivery
Bending
Carrying & Lifting Your Baby
Rocking
Holding Baby While Breastfeeding
Epidural Side Effects

30% of mothers report side effects, including injection site pain, weak core muscles, hip or back instability, sharp pain while standing or sitting, numbness or pain in the back.
Epidural back pain can make it harder to take care of baby. 

Breastfeeding moms are also often reluctant to take painkillers that might be passed along to the baby.
